answers.body_markdown:
Solved it by checking if the user has network connection before trying to do the import like this:

```js
function handleRoute(url) {
  if(&#39;onLine&#39; in navigator) {
    if(navigator.onLine) {
      // user is online, safe to import
      import(url);
    } else {
      // user is offline, don&#39;t even try to import -&gt; straight to `/offline`
      Router.go(&#39;/offline&#39;);
    }
  } else {
    // incase the browser doesnt support `navigator.onLine`, try to import anyway
    import(url);
  }
}
```

It _feels_ like a slightly hacky way to do it, but then again [browser support](https://caniuse.com/#search=navigator.onLine) for `navigator.onLine` is  pretty good.

For more information on retrying failed dynamic imports, I found [this](https://github.com/tc39/proposal-dynamic-import/issues/80) issue in the `tc39/proposal-dynamic-import` github repo.

